<p><b>What is the definition of human resource management with references?</b> Definition of Human Resource Management (HRM) Human resource management is organizing, coordinating, and managing an organization's current employees to carry out an organization's mission, vision, and goals. This includes recruiting, hiring, training, compensating, retaining, and motivating employees.</p>
<p><b>How many chapters are there in HRM?</b> </p>
<p><b>What is the foundation of human resource management?</b> It includes recruiting, screening, onboarding, training, performance management, and employee relations. HRM is responsible for developing, implementing, and monitoring policies, procedures, and programs to ensure the company complies with federal, state, and local laws and regulations.</p>
